INSERT INTO `wp_options` ( `option_id`, `option_name`, `option_value`, `autoload`) VALUES
(339, 'edd_sl_88d2d57a788b56dd81978557da7d274f', 'a:2:{s:7:"timeout";i:1772021267;s:5:"value";s:49979:"{"name":"Accessibility Checker","new_version":"1.20.0","stable_version":"1.20.0","sections":{"description":"<p>Accessibility Check Pro is a premium plugin that expands the free Accessibility Checker available in the WordPress.org plugin directory.\\nAccessibility Checker Pro adds vital features that allow comprehensive accessibility audits to be run within your WordPress dashboard.\\nFeatures include:<\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Full site scanning<\\/li>\\n<li>Ignore Log<\\/li>\\n<li>Bulk Ignore<\\/li>\\n<li>User restrictions on ignore<\\/li>\\n<li>Centralized list of all open issues<\\/li>\\n<li>Admin columns<\\/li>\\n<li>...and more<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p>Please note: Accessibility Checker Pro requires an active license to function. For a full list of features or to purchase a license, visit the\\n<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\">Accessibility Checker Pro website<\\/a>.<\\/p>","installation":"<p>Getting started with Accessibility Checker Pro is as easy as installing and activating the plugin, then configuring a few basic settings.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Installing Accessibility Checker Pro Within WordPress<\\/h3>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Visit the plugins page within your dashboard and select \\u2018Add New\\u2019.<\\/li>\\n<li>On the Add Plugins screen, click the \\"Upload Plugin\\" button.<\\/li>\\n<li>Upload the zipped plugin file from your download link.<\\/li>\\n<li>Activate Accessibility Checker Pro from your Plugins page.<\\/li>\\n<li>Follow the \\u2018after activation\\u2019 steps listed below.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ol>\\n<h3>Installing Accessibility Checker Pro Manually<\\/h3>\\n<p>1.Upload the unzipped \\u2018accessibility-checker\\u2019 folder to the \\/wp-content\\/plugins\\/ directory on your website via FTP.\\n2. Activate Accessibility Checker Pro from your Plugins page.\\n3. Follow the \\u2018after activation\\u2019 steps listed below.<\\/p>\\n<h3>After Activation<\\/h3>\\n<ol>\\n<li>If you do not have Accessibility Checker Free installed and active, Accessibility Checker Pro will prompt you to install and activate it. Follow the prompts to install Accessibility Checker.<\\/li>\\n<li>After activating the plugin, go to the Accessibility Checker settings page in your WordPress admin (found at \'\\/wp-admin\\/admin.php?page=accessibility_checker_settings\') to configure the\\nplugin settings.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ol>","changelog":"<h4> 1.20.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: sorting order on open issues tab is now by severity and count by default.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: fast track better shows that several of the same issue can exist on one page now.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.19.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Add: Sorting indicators to rule table headers.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Times now use a UTC helper function to ensure consistency across timezones.<\\/li>\\n<li>Tweaked: Set sslverify to true for license requests.<\\/li>\\n<li>Tweaked: Improved license messages and handling based on user capabilities.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.18.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Added a WP-CLI command to do license activations and deactivations for sites that use WP-CLI.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.17.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: Changed some icon file names to avoid spaces in file names.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Added additional security hardening when processing data passed in.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.16.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Archive scanning capability in full site scanner.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Can now scan Post Type Archives.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Can now scan Taxonomy Term Archives.<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Increased the scan posts cache time default from 5 min to 20 minutes.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.15.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Ability to filter post status that is scanned in full site scanner.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Improved licence key entering by including form on the plugins page.<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Resolved issue that blocked pausing or stopping the full site scan and restarting it immediately.<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Prevent php warning when pagination isn\'t possible on the log page.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Removed some unneeded settings for password protection (htaccess password is no longer a blocker for the scanner).<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.14.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Improved rule descriptions and metadata.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Landmark selector added to issues in tables<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Primary key added to global ignores table for better indexing<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.13.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Improved: translation issues with some JS strings<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: updated readme with security bug reporting information<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.12.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Removed: unused action hooks and related functions<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: untranslatable text<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: translation files<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: EDAC_ANWW_ACTIVE checks with ANWW_VERSION definition<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.11.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: updated call to remove str_get_html function with new edac_parse_html_for_media function.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.11.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Ability to filter by post status on the open issues page.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Swapped to more accurate scan rules that check the page more reliably.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Removed the need to run the first stage of the full site scan - this speeds up a full site scan by a large amount.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.10.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Handle notices better from the plugin.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.10.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Improved: Full site scan performance for very large sites with lots of metadata<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Add message for when fixes are changed in the open issues modal<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Use a more loose regex to detect file links for file size and type fix<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.9.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Issue with the ignore permission role handling<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Potential error when metadata was retrieved early<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.9.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Intorduced a new \'fixes\' system to help solve issues that the scanner detects.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Fix to ensure empty or missing  elements get added to the document.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Fix to block users from uploading pdf files without permission<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Fix to add file size and type to file links<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Fix to add missing form labels to form elements where they can be generated.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Added better aria labeling in some locations.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.8.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Don\'t reference button by color and instead reference by text.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.8.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Namespaced updater class could result in fatal error in some situations.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.8.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Enhancement: Performance improvements to full site scan - large sites will see big speed improvements<\\/li>\\n<li>Enhancement: Add a fail timeout in full site scan to prevent scan blocking on pages that error<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Surface pages that fail to scan in the full site scan<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Accessibility of select label on open issues page<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Accessibility of labels for fast track documentation links<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Accessibility of view pages and review issues buttons<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Prevent php warning when there is no pages to paginate on log page<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Resolved escaped html in the ignore text output<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Allow bulk ignores to handle very large batches of ignores with alt query<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.7.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: Tested up to WP 6.5.2<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: logic on asset loading<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: full site scan speed setting<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: full site scan API alert showing when no post types are selected<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.6.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: scan_start, scan_reset and scan_progress WP Rest API calls to replace admin-ajax calls<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: start-new-scan rest call<\\/li>\\n<li>Moved: <code>edacp_scan_start<\\/code> from accessibility-checker-pro to <code>EDACP\\\\Scans::start_php_scan<\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: <code>activation.php<\\/code> to use <code>EDACP\\\\Scans::start_php_scan<\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li>Deleted: CSS for log from full site scan page<\\/li>\\n<li>Moved: <code>getScanStats<\\/code> code from <code>\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/checkPages.js<\\/code> to <code>\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/fullSiteScanUI.js<\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li>Deleted: jquery from <code>\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/fullSiteScanUI.js<\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li>Added: a page reload every ten minutes to full site scan a page<\\/li>\\n<li>Deleted: setting authorization header in rest calls<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed:  mismatched number of URLs scanned<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: type in global ignore title<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: pluralization of full site summary stats<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.5.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: Audit History 1.0.0 and 1.0.1 update fix<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: variable casting<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.5.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: open issues descriptions output<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.5.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Issues with JavaScript assets not loading<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Full-site scan now supports JavaScript scanning<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: \'Stop\' button for full-site scanning<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Posts to scan function optimized for paging and using only IDs<\\/li>\\n<li>Removed: \'accessibility_checker_logs\' database table<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Code improvements in the database update function<\\/li>\\n<li>Removed: Full site scan log to enhance performance<\\/li>\\n<li>Removed: Background scan schedule to align with new full site scanning<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Full site scan completion message updated to reflect log removal<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.4.3 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: version and readme<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.4.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: readme<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.4.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: delete all data on uninstall option<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: misnamed authorization options and added migration function<\\/li>\\n<li>Update: password protection to pass authorization to wp-cron<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: expired license notice after key renews<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: image column to individual open issues and fast track<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: incorrect fieldname \\"objectid\\" in SQL call when clicking affected code in the table header on the issue log.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.4.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: adherence to coding standards<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: full-site scan stop button issue<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: settings page tab order<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: full-site scan error when no custom post types are configured for scanning in settings<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: activation issue when no custom post types are designated for scanning in settings<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: warnings when no custom post types are configured for scanning in settings<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: full-site scan completion date now uses site\'s localized timezone<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: refresh and caching for reports dashboard widget and welcome page<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.3.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed - scan log output<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed - ignore log not filtering by issue<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.3.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: plugin architecture for converting PHP checks to JavaScript<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: JavaScript scanning for color contrast check<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: full-site scan with a secondary JavaScript pass<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: full-site scan log output for better performance<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: full-site scan stop button<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: open issues table with accessibility improvements<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: frontend highlighting view on-page links<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.9 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: activation issue with the valid table name function and the dependency installer<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.8 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: issue with zip file name<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.7 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: filterable query limit to the full site scan log<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: full site scan to only run if a custom post type is selected in the settings<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: full site scan to delete data for post types no longer selected in the settings<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: bug with global ignores being added to all individually ignored issue count<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: usort deprecated notice on ignore log<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.6 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: open issues with no errors to show as passed<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Action Scheduler to latest version<\\/li>\\n<li>Update: Action Scheduler to load via Composer<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.5 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: post type count on full size scan<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.4 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: admin notice output<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.3 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: license tab<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: license check to run via cronjob<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: EDD license class<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: security updates<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: Support for the Restricted Access Plugin<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Password protection settings<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.2.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Update: Heading order on Open Issues, Fast Track, Ignore Log and Global Ignores pages<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Initial rule list page ordered by count to the Open Issues and Ignore Log pages<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Individual rule pages with count, issue summary and rule select to quickly switched between issues to the Open Issues and Ignore Log pages<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Custom Post Type select to Fast Track to reduce query load and improve performance<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.9 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Update dependency installer to latest version fixing dismiss-notice.js 404<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.8 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Update log filter admin url<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.7 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Show Open Issues and Ignore Log admin pages to users with ignore permissions<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.6 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Add support for PHP 8<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.5 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Move accessibility statement free plugin<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.4 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Update license domain and product name<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.3 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Improvements to license activation\\/deactivation settings<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Add support for Accessibility New Window Warning Plugin<\\/li>\\n<li>Plugin dependency installer<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fix to allow ignores database to be deleted on uninstall<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.1.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fast Track<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.0.3 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updates to database creation\\/updates<\\/li>\\n<li>Updates to plugin updater<\\/li>\\n<li>Deprecated jQuery fixes<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.0.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Full site scan and background scan<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.0.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Removed content hook<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed issue with log search if post type has been Removed<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed duplicate column names in screen options<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.0.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Everything is new and shiny.<\\/li>\\n<li>We think it\'s awesome you want to make your website more accessible.<\\/li>\\n<li>Thank you for purchasing Accessibility Checker Pro.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>","faq":"<h4>What support is included?<\\/h4>\\n<p>Equalize Digital provides free personalized support on plugin usage and features via email for all license holders. This includes information about functionality and\\ntroubleshooting assistance. You may <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/support\\/pro-support\\/\\">open a support ticket<\\/a> at any time. Plugin support is limited to\\nproviding assistance in using the plugin but does not include support resolving any specific accessibility issues that have been identified.<\\/p>\\n<h4>Can you help me figure out how to fix an error or warning on my website?<\\/h4>\\n<p>If you have questions about specific errors and warnings on your website or need help fixing problems, we offer <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/priority-support\\/\\">priority support packages<\\/a>\\nthat include full (phone and email) access to our accessibility specialists and developers. If you need more in-depth auditing, user testing, and remediation, or would like to\\nget your website certified as accessible, <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/equalizedigital.com\\/\\">we can help with that too<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\n<h4>Do I lose functionality if my license key is not active?<\\/h4>\\n<p>To utilize Accessibility Checker Pro features, receive plugin updates, and support, you do need to have an active license key. If your license key has expired, you can\\ncontinue to use the free version of Accessibility Checker but will lose access to Pro features.<\\/p>\\n<h4>How can I report security bugs?<\\/h4>\\n<p>You can report security bugs through the Patchstack Vulnerability Disclosure Program. The Patchstack team helps validate, triage and handle any security vulnerabilities. <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/patchstack.com\\/database\\/vdp\\/9e5fbe42-43e5-4644-89f5-04340fd263a4\\">Report a security vulnerability.<\\/a><\\/p>\\n"},"license_check":"","msg":"","homepage":"https:\\/\\/a11ychecker.com","package":"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/edd-sl\\/package_download\\/MTc3MjI0ODA2Nzo1OGJiYTIwY2Q2ZTUyYTQ0YWNhMGJmOTQwNmRlNDczYzoyNDo5ZGM2OWZhYTZhY2RjOGFiZjdjNjRjNWI3MGY5NmQ1YzpodHRwc0AvL2JlcmtoYW1jb3Vucy53cGVuZ2luZXBvd2VyZWQuY29tOjA=","icons":[],"banners":{"high":"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/4\\/edd\\/2020\\/12\\/plugin-banner-large.png","low":"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/4\\/edd\\/2020\\/12\\/plugin-banner-small.png"},"slug":"accessibility-checker-pro","url":"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/downloads\\/accessibility-checker-pro\\/?changelog=1","last_updated":"2026-02-13 18:11:25","download_link":"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/edd-sl\\/package_download\\/MTc3MjI0ODA2Nzo1OGJiYTIwY2Q2ZTUyYTQ0YWNhMGJmOTQwNmRlNDczYzoyNDo5ZGM2OWZhYTZhY2RjOGFiZjdjNjRjNWI3MGY5NmQ1YzpodHRwc0AvL2JlcmtoYW1jb3Vucy53cGVuZ2luZXBvd2VyZWQuY29tOjA=","tags":["accessibility","accessible","wcag","ada","a11y"],"requires":"6.2","tested":"6.8","requires_php":"","contributors":{"equalizedigital":{"display_name":"equalizedigital","profile":"\\/\\/profiles.wordpress.org\\/equalizedigital","avatar":"https:\\/\\/wordpress.org\\/grav-redirect.php?user=equalizedigital"},"alh0319":{"display_name":"alh0319","profile":"\\/\\/profiles.wordpress.org\\/alh0319","avatar":"https:\\/\\/wordpress.org\\/grav-redirect.php?user=alh0319"},"stevejonesdev":{"display_name":"stevejonesdev","profile":"\\/\\/profiles.wordpress.org\\/stevejonesdev","avatar":"https:\\/\\/wordpress.org\\/grav-redirect.php?user=stevejonesdev"}},"stable_tag":"1.20.0","donate_link":"","short_description":"This plugin adds pro features to the Acessibility Checker plugin, including full site scanning.","license":"GPLv2 or later","upgrade_notice":"","screenshots":[],"faq":["<h4>What support is included?<\\/h4>\\n<p>Equalize Digital provides free personalized support on plugin usage and features via email for all license holders. This includes information about functionality and\\ntroubleshooting assistance. You may <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/support\\/pro-support\\/\\">open a support ticket<\\/a> at any time. Plugin support is limited to\\nproviding assistance in using the plugin but does not include support resolving any specific accessibility issues that have been identified.<\\/p>\\n<h4>Can you help me figure out how to fix an error or warning on my website?<\\/h4>\\n<p>If you have questions about specific errors and warnings on your website or need help fixing problems, we offer <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/priority-support\\/\\">priority support packages<\\/a>\\nthat include full (phone and email) access to our accessibility specialists and developers. If you need more in-depth auditing, user testing, and remediation, or would like to\\nget your website certified as accessible, <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/equalizedigital.com\\/\\">we can help with that too<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\n<h4>Do I lose functionality if my license key is not active?<\\/h4>\\n<p>To utilize Accessibility Checker Pro features, receive plugin updates, and support, you do need to have an active license key. If your license key has expired, you can\\ncontinue to use the free version of Accessibility Checker but will lose access to Pro features.<\\/p>\\n<h4>How can I report security bugs?<\\/h4>\\n<p>You can report security bugs through the Patchstack Vulnerability Disclosure Program. The Patchstack team helps validate, triage and handle any security vulnerabilities. <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/patchstack.com\\/database\\/vdp\\/9e5fbe42-43e5-4644-89f5-04340fd263a4\\">Report a security vulnerability.<\\/a><\\/p>\\n"],"warnings":{"too_many_tags":["section 508","audit","readability","content analysis"]},"expected_sections":["description","installation","faq","screenshots","changelog","upgrade_notice","other_notes"],"alias_sections":{"frequently_asked_questions":"faq","change_log":"changelog","screenshot":"screenshots"},"valid_headers":{"tested":"tested","tested up to":"tested","requires":"requires","requires at least":"requires","requires php":"requires_php","tags":"tags","contributors":"contributors","donate link":"donate_link","stable tag":"stable_tag","license":"license","license uri":"license_uri"},"ignore_tags":["plugin","wordpress"],"maximum_field_lengths":{"short_description":150,"section":2500,"section-changelog":5000,"section-faq":5000},"raw_contents":"=== Accessibility Checker Pro ===\\nContributors: equalizedigital, alh0319, stevejonesdev\\nTags: accessibility, accessible, wcag, ada, a11y, section 508, audit, readability, content analysis\\nRequires at least: 6.2\\nTested up to: 6.8\\nStable tag: 1.20.0\\nLicense: GPLv2 or later\\nLicense URI: http:\\/\\/www.gnu.org\\/licenses\\/gpl-2.0.html\\n\\n\\nThis plugin adds pro features to the Acessibility Checker plugin, including full site scanning.\\n\\n== Description ==\\n\\nAccessibility Check Pro is a premium plugin that expands the free Accessibility Checker available in the WordPress.org plugin directory.\\nAccessibility Checker Pro adds vital features that allow comprehensive accessibility audits to be run within your WordPress dashboard.\\nFeatures include:\\n\\n* Full site scanning\\n* Ignore Log\\n* Bulk Ignore\\n* User restrictions on ignore\\n* Centralized list of all open issues\\n* Admin columns\\n* ...and more\\n\\nPlease note: Accessibility Checker Pro requires an active license to function. For a full list of features or to purchase a license, visit the\\n[Accessibility Checker Pro website](https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com).\\n\\n== Installation ==\\nGetting started with Accessibility Checker Pro is as easy as installing and activating the plugin, then configuring a few basic settings.\\n\\n### Installing Accessibility Checker Pro Within WordPress\\n1. Visit the plugins page within your dashboard and select \\u2018Add New\\u2019.\\n2. On the Add Plugins screen, click the \\"Upload Plugin\\" button.\\n3. Upload the zipped plugin file from your download link.\\n4. Activate Accessibility Checker Pro from your Plugins page.\\n5. Follow the \\u2018after activation\\u2019 steps listed below.\\n\\n### Installing Accessibility Checker Pro Manually\\n\\n1.Upload the unzipped \\u2018accessibility-checker\\u2019 folder to the \\/wp-content\\/plugins\\/ directory on your website via FTP.\\n2. Activate Accessibility Checker Pro from your Plugins page.\\n3. Follow the \\u2018after activation\\u2019 steps listed below.\\n\\n### After Activation\\n1. If you do not have Accessibility Checker Free installed and active, Accessibility Checker Pro will prompt you to install and activate it. Follow the prompts to install Accessibility Checker.\\n2. After activating the plugin, go to the Accessibility Checker settings page in your WordPress admin (found at \'\\/wp-admin\\/admin.php?page=accessibility_checker_settings\') to configure the\\nplugin settings.\\n\\n== Frequently Asked Questions ==\\n\\n= What support is included? =\\n\\nEqualize Digital provides free personalized support on plugin usage and features via email for all license holders. This includes information about functionality and\\ntroubleshooting assistance. You may [open a support ticket](https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/support\\/pro-support\\/) at any time. Plugin support is limited to\\nproviding assistance in using the plugin but does not include support resolving any specific accessibility issues that have been identified.\\n\\n= Can you help me figure out how to fix an error or warning on my website? =\\n\\nIf you have questions about specific errors and warnings on your website or need help fixing problems, we offer [priority support packages](https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\/priority-support\\/)\\nthat include full (phone and email) access to our accessibility specialists and developers. If you need more in-depth auditing, user testing, and remediation, or would like to\\nget your website certified as accessible, [we can help with that too](https:\\/\\/equalizedigital.com\\/).\\n\\n= Do I lose functionality if my license key is not active? =\\n\\nTo utilize Accessibility Checker Pro features, receive plugin updates, and support, you do need to have an active license key. If your license key has expired, you can\\ncontinue to use the free version of Accessibility Checker but will lose access to Pro features.\\n\\n= How can I report security bugs? =\\n\\nYou can report security bugs through the Patchstack Vulnerability Disclosure Program. The Patchstack team helps validate, triage and handle any security vulnerabilities. [Report a security vulnerability.](https:\\/\\/patchstack.com\\/database\\/vdp\\/9e5fbe42-43e5-4644-89f5-04340fd263a4)\\n\\n== Changelog ==\\n\\n= 1.20.0 =\\n* Fixed: sorting order on open issues tab is now by severity and count by default.\\n* Improved: fast track better shows that several of the same issue can exist on one page now.\\n\\n= 1.19.0 =\\n* Add: Sorting indicators to rule table headers.\\n* Improved: Times now use a UTC helper function to ensure consistency across timezones.\\n* Tweaked: Set sslverify to true for license requests.\\n* Tweaked: Improved license messages and handling based on user capabilities.\\n\\n= 1.18.0 =\\n* New: Added a WP-CLI command to do license activations and deactivations for sites that use WP-CLI.\\n\\n= 1.17.0 =\\n* Updated: Changed some icon file names to avoid spaces in file names.\\n* Improved: Added additional security hardening when processing data passed in.\\n\\n= 1.16.0 =\\n* New: Archive scanning capability in full site scanner.\\n* New: Can now scan Post Type Archives.\\n* New: Can now scan Taxonomy Term Archives.\\n* Updated: Increased the scan posts cache time default from 5 min to 20 minutes.\\n\\n= 1.15.0 =\\n* New: Ability to filter post status that is scanned in full site scanner.\\n* New: Improved licence key entering by including form on the plugins page.\\n* Fixed: Resolved issue that blocked pausing or stopping the full site scan and restarting it immediately.\\n* Fixed: Prevent php warning when pagination isn\'t possible on the log page.\\n* Improved: Removed some unneeded settings for password protection (htaccess password is no longer a blocker for the scanner).\\n\\n= 1.14.0 =\\n* New: Improved rule descriptions and metadata.\\n* New: Landmark selector added to issues in tables\\n* Added: Primary key added to global ignores table for better indexing\\n\\n= 1.13.0 =\\n* Improved: translation issues with some JS strings\\n* Improved: updated readme with security bug reporting information\\n\\n= 1.12.0 =\\n* Removed: unused action hooks and related functions\\n* Fixed: untranslatable text\\n* Added: translation files\\n* Updated: EDAC_ANWW_ACTIVE checks with ANWW_VERSION definition\\n\\n= 1.11.1 =\\n* Fixed: updated call to remove str_get_html function with new edac_parse_html_for_media function.\\n\\n= 1.11.0 =\\n* New: Ability to filter by post status on the open issues page.\\n* Improved: Swapped to more accurate scan rules that check the page more reliably.\\n* Improved: Removed the need to run the first stage of the full site scan - this speeds up a full site scan by a large amount.\\n\\n= 1.10.1 =\\n* Fixed: Handle notices better from the plugin.\\n\\n= 1.10.0 =\\n* Improved: Full site scan performance for very large sites with lots of metadata\\n* Improved: Add message for when fixes are changed in the open issues modal\\n* Fixed: Use a more loose regex to detect file links for file size and type fix\\n\\n= 1.9.1 =\\n* Fixed: Issue with the ignore permission role handling\\n* Fixed: Potential error when metadata was retrieved early\\n\\n= 1.9.0 =\\n* New: Intorduced a new \'fixes\' system to help solve issues that the scanner detects.\\n* New: Fix to ensure empty or missing <title> elements get added to the document.\\n* New: Fix to block users from uploading pdf files without permission\\n* New: Fix to add file size and type to file links\\n* New: Fix to add missing form labels to form elements where they can be generated.\\n* Improved: Added better aria labeling in some locations.\\n\\n= 1.8.2 =\\n* Fixed: Don\'t reference button by color and instead reference by text.\\n\\n= 1.8.1 =\\n* Fixed: Namespaced updater class could result in fatal error in some situations.\\n\\n= 1.8.0 =\\n* Enhancement: Performance improvements to full site scan - large sites will see big speed improvements\\n* Enhancement: Add a fail timeout in full site scan to prevent scan blocking on pages that error\\n* Added: Surface pages that fail to scan in the full site scan\\n* Improved: Accessibility of select label on open issues page\\n* Improved: Accessibility of labels for fast track documentation links\\n* Improved: Accessibility of view pages and review issues buttons\\n* Fixed: Prevent php warning when there is no pages to paginate on log page\\n* Fixed: Resolved escaped html in the ignore text output\\n* Fixed: Allow bulk ignores to handle very large batches of ignores with alt query\\n\\n= 1.7.0 =\\n* Updated: Tested up to WP 6.5.2\\n* Updated: logic on asset loading\\n* Added: full site scan speed setting\\n* Fixed: full site scan API alert showing when no post types are selected\\n\\n= 1.6.0 =\\n* Added: scan_start, scan_reset and scan_progress WP Rest API calls to replace admin-ajax calls\\n* Added: start-new-scan rest call\\n* Moved: `edacp_scan_start` from accessibility-checker-pro to `EDACP\\\\Scans::start_php_scan`\\n* Updated: `activation.php` to use `EDACP\\\\Scans::start_php_scan`\\n* Deleted: CSS for log from full site scan page\\n* Moved: `getScanStats` code from `\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/checkPages.js` to `\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/fullSiteScanUI.js`\\n* Deleted: jquery from `\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/fullSiteScanUI.js`\\n* Added: a page reload every ten minutes to full site scan a page\\n* Deleted: setting authorization header in rest calls\\n* Fixed:  mismatched number of URLs scanned\\n* Fixed: type in global ignore title\\n* Fixed: pluralization of full site summary stats\\n\\n= 1.5.2 =\\n* Added: Audit History 1.0.0 and 1.0.1 update fix\\n* Fixed: variable casting\\n\\n= 1.5.1 =\\n* Fixed: open issues descriptions output\\n\\n= 1.5.0 =\\n* Fixed: Issues with JavaScript assets not loading\\n* Updated: Full-site scan now supports JavaScript scanning\\n* Added: \'Stop\' button for full-site scanning\\n* Updated: Posts to scan function optimized for paging and using only IDs\\n* Removed: \'accessibility_checker_logs\' database table\\n* Added: Code improvements in the database update function\\n* Removed: Full site scan log to enhance performance\\n* Removed: Background scan schedule to align with new full site scanning\\n* Updated: Full site scan completion message updated to reflect log removal\\n\\n= 1.4.3 =\\n* Updated: version and readme\\n\\n= 1.4.2 =\\n* Updated: readme\\n\\n= 1.4.1 =\\n* Fixed: delete all data on uninstall option\\n* Fixed: misnamed authorization options and added migration function\\n* Update: password protection to pass authorization to wp-cron\\n* Fixed: expired license notice after key renews\\n* Added: image column to individual open issues and fast track\\n* Fixed: incorrect fieldname \\"objectid\\" in SQL call when clicking affected code in the table header on the issue log.\\n\\n= 1.4.0 =\\n* Fixed: adherence to coding standards\\n* Fixed: full-site scan stop button issue\\n* Fixed: settings page tab order\\n* Fixed: full-site scan error when no custom post types are configured for scanning in settings\\n* Fixed: activation issue when no custom post types are designated for scanning in settings\\n* Added: warnings when no custom post types are configured for scanning in settings\\n* Updated: full-site scan completion date now uses site\'s localized timezone\\n* Updated: refresh and caching for reports dashboard widget and welcome page\\n\\n= 1.3.1 =\\n* Fixed - scan log output\\n* Fixed - ignore log not filtering by issue\\n\\n= 1.3.0 =\\n* Added: plugin architecture for converting PHP checks to JavaScript\\n* Added: JavaScript scanning for color contrast check\\n* Updated: full-site scan with a secondary JavaScript pass\\n* Updated: full-site scan log output for better performance\\n* Added: full-site scan stop button\\n* Updated: open issues table with accessibility improvements\\n* Added: frontend highlighting view on-page links\\n\\n= 1.2.9 =\\n* Fixed: activation issue with the valid table name function and the dependency installer\\n\\n= 1.2.8 =\\n* Fixed: issue with zip file name\\n\\n= 1.2.7 =\\n* Added: filterable query limit to the full site scan log\\n* Updated: full site scan to only run if a custom post type is selected in the settings\\n* Updated: full site scan to delete data for post types no longer selected in the settings\\n* Fixed: bug with global ignores being added to all individually ignored issue count\\n* Fixed: usort deprecated notice on ignore log\\n\\n= 1.2.6 =\\n* Fixed: open issues with no errors to show as passed\\n* Updated: Action Scheduler to latest version\\n* Update: Action Scheduler to load via Composer\\n\\n= 1.2.5 =\\n* Fixed: post type count on full size scan\\n\\n= 1.2.4 =\\n* Updated: admin notice output\\n\\n= 1.2.3 =\\n* Added: license tab\\n* Updated: license check to run via cronjob\\n* Updated: EDD license class\\n\\n= 1.2.2 =\\n* Added: security updates\\n\\n= 1.2.1 =\\n* Added: Support for the Restricted Access Plugin\\n* Added: Password protection settings\\n\\n= 1.2.0 =\\n* Update: Heading order on Open Issues, Fast Track, Ignore Log and Global Ignores pages\\n* Added: Initial rule list page ordered by count to the Open Issues and Ignore Log pages\\n* Added: Individual rule pages with count, issue summary and rule select to quickly switched between issues to the Open Issues and Ignore Log pages\\n* Added: Custom Post Type select to Fast Track to reduce query load and improve performance\\n\\n= 1.1.9 =\\n* Update dependency installer to latest version fixing dismiss-notice.js 404\\n\\n= 1.1.8 =\\n* Update log filter admin url\\n\\n= 1.1.7 =\\n* Show Open Issues and Ignore Log admin pages to users with ignore permissions\\n\\n= 1.1.6 =\\n* Add support for PHP 8\\n\\n= 1.1.5 =\\n* Move accessibility statement free plugin\\n\\n= 1.1.4 =\\n* Update license domain and product name\\n\\n= 1.1.3 =\\n* Improvements to license activation\\/deactivation settings\\n\\n= 1.1.2 =\\n* Add support for Accessibility New Window Warning Plugin\\n* Plugin dependency installer\\n\\n= 1.1.1 =\\n* Fix to allow ignores database to be deleted on uninstall\\n\\n= 1.1.0 =\\n* Fast Track\\n\\n= 1.0.3 =\\n* Updates to database creation\\/updates\\n* Updates to plugin updater\\n* Deprecated jQuery fixes\\n\\n= 1.0.2 =\\n* Full site scan and background scan\\n\\n= 1.0.1 =\\n* Removed content hook\\n* Fixed issue with log search if post type has been Removed\\n* Fixed duplicate column names in screen options\\n\\n= 1.0.0 =\\n* Everything is new and shiny.\\n* We think it\'s awesome you want to make your website more accessible.\\n* Thank you for purchasing Accessibility Checker Pro.\\n","description":["<p>Accessibility Check Pro is a premium plugin that expands the free Accessibility Checker available in the WordPress.org plugin directory.\\nAccessibility Checker Pro adds vital features that allow comprehensive accessibility audits to be run within your WordPress dashboard.\\nFeatures include:<\\/p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Full site scanning<\\/li>\\n<li>Ignore Log<\\/li>\\n<li>Bulk Ignore<\\/li>\\n<li>User restrictions on ignore<\\/li>\\n<li>Centralized list of all open issues<\\/li>\\n<li>Admin columns<\\/li>\\n<li>...and more<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<p>Please note: Accessibility Checker Pro requires an active license to function. For a full list of features or to purchase a license, visit the\\n<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/my.equalizedigital.com\\">Accessibility Checker Pro website<\\/a>.<\\/p>"],"installation":["<p>Getting started with Accessibility Checker Pro is as easy as installing and activating the plugin, then configuring a few basic settings.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Installing Accessibility Checker Pro Within WordPress<\\/h3>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Visit the plugins page within your dashboard and select \\u2018Add New\\u2019.<\\/li>\\n<li>On the Add Plugins screen, click the \\"Upload Plugin\\" button.<\\/li>\\n<li>Upload the zipped plugin file from your download link.<\\/li>\\n<li>Activate Accessibility Checker Pro from your Plugins page.<\\/li>\\n<li>Follow the \\u2018after activation\\u2019 steps listed below.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ol>\\n<h3>Installing Accessibility Checker Pro Manually<\\/h3>\\n<p>1.Upload the unzipped \\u2018accessibility-checker\\u2019 folder to the \\/wp-content\\/plugins\\/ directory on your website via FTP.\\n2. Activate Accessibility Checker Pro from your Plugins page.\\n3. Follow the \\u2018after activation\\u2019 steps listed below.<\\/p>\\n<h3>After Activation<\\/h3>\\n<ol>\\n<li>If you do not have Accessibility Checker Free installed and active, Accessibility Checker Pro will prompt you to install and activate it. Follow the prompts to install Accessibility Checker.<\\/li>\\n<li>After activating the plugin, go to the Accessibility Checker settings page in your WordPress admin (found at \'\\/wp-admin\\/admin.php?page=accessibility_checker_settings\') to configure the\\nplugin settings.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ol>"],"changelog":["<h4> 1.20.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: sorting order on open issues tab is now by severity and count by default.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: fast track better shows that several of the same issue can exist on one page now.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.19.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Add: Sorting indicators to rule table headers.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Times now use a UTC helper function to ensure consistency across timezones.<\\/li>\\n<li>Tweaked: Set sslverify to true for license requests.<\\/li>\\n<li>Tweaked: Improved license messages and handling based on user capabilities.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.18.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Added a WP-CLI command to do license activations and deactivations for sites that use WP-CLI.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.17.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: Changed some icon file names to avoid spaces in file names.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Added additional security hardening when processing data passed in.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.16.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Archive scanning capability in full site scanner.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Can now scan Post Type Archives.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Can now scan Taxonomy Term Archives.<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Increased the scan posts cache time default from 5 min to 20 minutes.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.15.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Ability to filter post status that is scanned in full site scanner.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Improved licence key entering by including form on the plugins page.<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Resolved issue that blocked pausing or stopping the full site scan and restarting it immediately.<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Prevent php warning when pagination isn\'t possible on the log page.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Removed some unneeded settings for password protection (htaccess password is no longer a blocker for the scanner).<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.14.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Improved rule descriptions and metadata.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Landmark selector added to issues in tables<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Primary key added to global ignores table for better indexing<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.13.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Improved: translation issues with some JS strings<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: updated readme with security bug reporting information<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.12.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Removed: unused action hooks and related functions<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: untranslatable text<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: translation files<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: EDAC_ANWW_ACTIVE checks with ANWW_VERSION definition<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.11.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: updated call to remove str_get_html function with new edac_parse_html_for_media function.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.11.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Ability to filter by post status on the open issues page.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Swapped to more accurate scan rules that check the page more reliably.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Removed the need to run the first stage of the full site scan - this speeds up a full site scan by a large amount.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.10.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Handle notices better from the plugin.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.10.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Improved: Full site scan performance for very large sites with lots of metadata<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Add message for when fixes are changed in the open issues modal<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Use a more loose regex to detect file links for file size and type fix<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.9.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Issue with the ignore permission role handling<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Potential error when metadata was retrieved early<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.9.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>New: Intorduced a new \'fixes\' system to help solve issues that the scanner detects.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Fix to ensure empty or missing  elements get added to the document.<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Fix to block users from uploading pdf files without permission<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Fix to add file size and type to file links<\\/li>\\n<li>New: Fix to add missing form labels to form elements where they can be generated.<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Added better aria labeling in some locations.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.8.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Don\'t reference button by color and instead reference by text.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.8.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Namespaced updater class could result in fatal error in some situations.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.8.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Enhancement: Performance improvements to full site scan - large sites will see big speed improvements<\\/li>\\n<li>Enhancement: Add a fail timeout in full site scan to prevent scan blocking on pages that error<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Surface pages that fail to scan in the full site scan<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Accessibility of select label on open issues page<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Accessibility of labels for fast track documentation links<\\/li>\\n<li>Improved: Accessibility of view pages and review issues buttons<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Prevent php warning when there is no pages to paginate on log page<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Resolved escaped html in the ignore text output<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: Allow bulk ignores to handle very large batches of ignores with alt query<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.7.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: Tested up to WP 6.5.2<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: logic on asset loading<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: full site scan speed setting<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: full site scan API alert showing when no post types are selected<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.6.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: scan_start, scan_reset and scan_progress WP Rest API calls to replace admin-ajax calls<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: start-new-scan rest call<\\/li>\\n<li>Moved: <code>edacp_scan_start<\\/code> from accessibility-checker-pro to <code>EDACP\\\\Scans::start_php_scan<\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: <code>activation.php<\\/code> to use <code>EDACP\\\\Scans::start_php_scan<\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li>Deleted: CSS for log from full site scan page<\\/li>\\n<li>Moved: <code>getScanStats<\\/code> code from <code>\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/checkPages.js<\\/code> to <code>\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/fullSiteScanUI.js<\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li>Deleted: jquery from <code>\\/src\\/fullSiteScanApp\\/fullSiteScanUI.js<\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li>Added: a page reload every ten minutes to full site scan a page<\\/li>\\n<li>Deleted: setting authorization header in rest calls<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed:  mismatched number of URLs scanned<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: type in global ignore title<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: pluralization of full site summary stats<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.5.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: Audit History 1.0.0 and 1.0.1 update fix<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: variable casting<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.5.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: open issues descriptions output<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.5.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: Issues with JavaScript assets not loading<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Full-site scan now supports JavaScript scanning<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: \'Stop\' button for full-site scanning<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Posts to scan function optimized for paging and using only IDs<\\/li>\\n<li>Removed: \'accessibility_checker_logs\' database table<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: Code improvements in the database update function<\\/li>\\n<li>Removed: Full site scan log to enhance performance<\\/li>\\n<li>Removed: Background scan schedule to align with new full site scanning<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: Full site scan completion message updated to reflect log removal<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.4.3 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: version and readme<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.4.2 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Updated: readme<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.4.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: delete all data on uninstall option<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: misnamed authorization options and added migration function<\\/li>\\n<li>Update: password protection to pass authorization to wp-cron<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: expired license notice after key renews<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: image column to individual open issues and fast track<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: incorrect fieldname \\"objectid\\" in SQL call when clicking affected code in the table header on the issue log.<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.4.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed: adherence to coding standards<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: full-site scan stop button issue<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: settings page tab order<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: full-site scan error when no custom post types are configured for scanning in settings<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed: activation issue when no custom post types are designated for scanning in settings<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: warnings when no custom post types are configured for scanning in settings<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: full-site scan completion date now uses site\'s localized timezone<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: refresh and caching for reports dashboard widget and welcome page<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.3.1 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Fixed - scan log output<\\/li>\\n<li>Fixed - ignore log not filtering by issue<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n<h4> 1.3.0 <\\/h4>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Added: plugin architecture for converting PHP checks to JavaScript<\\/li>\\n<li>Added: JavaScript scanning for color contrast check<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: full-site scan with a secondary JavaScript pass<\\/li>\\n<li>Updated: full-site scan log output for better performance<\\/li>